&nbsp;The summit convened to provide an opportunity for all 10 countries using the River Nile waters to agree on how to equitably use the resource. However, the first signs that all was not well emerged when news filtered through that&nbsp; Sudanese President Omar al-Bashir and his South Sudan counterpart Salva Kiir would skip the event, writes Abubaker Mayemba & Johnson Taremwa for The Obsever.